commit.message: Use HTTP.newManager instead of deprecated HTTP.withManager

convert deprecated conduit operators

Avoids some build warnings.

$= and =$= are the same and .| replaces them

The $$ deprecation message is "Use runConduit and .|" but I'm
not clear how to as a non-user of conduit. But I noticed that
conduit still contains connect = ($$) which is not deprecated.
So use that. Unfortunately, it has a different precidence than
the $$ operator, so have to add parens.

conduit deprecated Producer, Source, Sink, Conduit

avoid build warnings by converting to ConduitT

type Producer m o = forall i. ConduitT i o m ()
type Source m o = ConduitT () o m ()
type Sink i = ConduitT i Void
type Conduit i m o = ConduitT i o m ()

The deprecations were already present in conduit-1.3.0, the oldest
version the deps allow.

avoid build warnings

Imports of Control.Applicative and Data.Monoid are not
needed with modern versions of ghc, but are still done explicitly to
keep it building with old versions of ghc. To avoid build warnings about
those unncessary imports, import Prelude explicitly.

StarIsType conversion

This avoids a build warning about StarIsType being slated for
deprecation.

base-4.9 (ghc-8.0.1) is needed for Data.Kind.

add s3Region constructor to S3Configuration

This supports custom regions used by S3 implementations other than AWS.

Bumping version to 0.24 since adding a constructor risks breaking code.

consistent layout of multi-line constructor

There were 3 different layouts used in 3 places for S3Configuration.
It may not be consistent throughout the code base, but this is surely an
improvement.
Allow bytestring 0.11

avoid build warnings

Imports of Control.Applicative, Data.Monoid, and Data.Functor are not
needed with modern versions of ghc, but are still done explicitly to
keep it building with old versions of ghc. To avoid build warnings about
those unncessary imports, import Prelude explicitly, and avoid importing
particular functions from them.

fix build warnings

Fixes "No variables bound in the record wildcard match are used"

convert some tabs

Fixes a build warning and the tabs were mixed with spaces in a not good
way even if you like tabs.
fix build warning for redundant export of isAnonymousCredentials
prepare 0.23

support S3 access without credentials, by using anonymousCredentials

This allows using GetBucket and GetObject against a public S3 bucket.
Other actions may also work for the rare bucket that supports
unauthenticated writes.

anonymousCredentials generates a Credentials with the access key and
secret key both empty. So AWS requests that do not support anonymous
access will proceed the same ways that they currently do when the user
sets AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID="" and AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY="". Eg, the AWS
server will reject the request because it is not properly signed.

isAnonymousCredentials was added as a field of Credentials to allow
differentiating between anonymousCredentials being used, and the user
providing empty credentials. This avoids a behavior change when the user
provides empty credentials to a program that uses S3. The new
constructor means that the version needs to be bumped to eg 0.23.

I first considered adding a NoCredentials constructor to Credentials.
But that would need to be checked for throughout the code base everywhere
that fields of Credentials are accessed. And adding that constructor
did not really add any type safety.
prepare 0.22.1

allow attoparsec-0.14 and base16-bytestring-1.0 to support lts-19.16

The stack.yaml needed to be updated to one that has aeson-2 after
bumping that dependency. And that required supporting newer
versions of attoparsec and base16-bytestring.

I've reviewed the changelogs and tested a build with stack, and the
existing code works ok with those.
